ok, B.W., (2006) Southeast Asian Biodiversity in Crisis, , Cambridge: Cambridge University Press; Sodhi, N.S., Brook, B.W., Bradshaw, C.J.A., (2007) Tropical Conservation Biology, , Oxford: Blackwell; Sodhi, N.S., Lee, T.M., Sekercioglu, C.H., Webb, E.L., Prawiradilaga, D.W., Lohman, D.J., Pierce, N.E., Ehrlich, P.R., Local people value environmental services provided by forested parks (2010) Biodivers Conserv (this volume), , doi: 10. 1007/s10531-009-9745-9; Sosdian, S., Rosenthal, Y., Deep-sea temperature and ice volume changes across the Pliocene-Pleistocene climate transitions (2009) Science, 325, pp. 306-310; Spalding, M.D., Green, E.P., Ravilious, C., (2001) World Atlas of Coral Reefs, , Berkeley: University of California Press; Srikwan, S., Woodruff, D.S., Genetic erosion in isolated small mammal populations following rain forest fragmentation (2000) Genetics Demography and Viability of Fragmented Populations, pp. 149-172. , A. Young and G. Clarke (Eds.), Cambridge: Cambridge University Press; Srikwan, S., Jakobsson, M., Albrecht, A., Dalkilic, M., Trust establishment in data sharing: An incentive model for biodiversity information systems (2006) TrustCol, 2006, pp. 1-8; Sterling, E.J., Hurley, M.M., Minh, L.D., (2006) Vietnam: A Natural History, , New Haven: Yale University Press; Taylor, D., Biomass fires, humans and climate change in Southeast Asia (2010) Biodivers Conserv (this volume), , doi: 10. 1007/s10531-009-9756-6; Tougard, C., Montuire, S., Pleistocene paleoenvironmental reconstructions and mammalian evolution in South-East Asia: Focus on fossil faunas from Thailand (2006) Quat Sci Rev, 25, pp. 126-141; (2008) Tonle Sap conservation project, , UNDP, Project Fact Sheet 01/2008 (project 00038552). UNDP Cambodia; van Steenis, C.G.G.J., The delimitation of Malesia and its main plant geographical divisions (1950) Flora Malesiana, I (1), pp. lxx-lxxv; Wallace, A.R., (1876) The Geographical Distribution of Animals, , London: Macmillan; Wang, X.M., Sun, X.